    "body": "My comments from IRC:\n\n```\n17:25 < pchote> reaperrr: cruiser and msub will want to search for targets on land\n17:25 < pchote> and destroyers for air targets\n17:26 < pchote> reaperrr: it would be great if you could assign protection squads\n17:26 < pchote> so you could have a squad that is a cruiser that targets land, \n                and then a support squad of destroyers and gunboats that guard it\n17:27 < pchote> that would also work well for engineer squads etc\n17:27 < pchote> we'll also want a key for a squad behaviour module\n17:27 < pchote> defaulting to whatever we use now\n17:28 < pchote> we can then have special case modules for thumpers, engineers, \n                harvesters, mcvs\n17:29 < pchote> hmm... that would probably also cover the guard idea too\n17:29 < pchote> what you have looks like a great starting point\n17:30 < reaperrr> I wrote this mockup with the status quo in mind (\"I try to \n                  AttackMove towards targets I can't reach\" issue not fixed), of \n                  course it would be better if we adressed that as well\n17:30 < pchote> yeah\n17:31 < pchote> my suggestions above are definitely a phase two suggestion\n17:31 < pchote> but it would be good to set it up in a way to support it\n```\n"
